What the contract does:
The contract lets me withdraw my funds.
The vulnerability:
The condition for withdrawal was "require(balances[msg.sender] - _value >= 0)".
The problem with this is that if balances[msg.sender] < _value, underflow will happen and the value balances[msg.sender] - _value will become greater than ), and almost always a huge no., which will likely drain all of the funds held by that contract.
How I exploited it:
I transferred 21 tokens to an address. The balance in my account did the math 20-21 and went through an underflow and gave me 2^256-1 tokens.
Prevention:
Always use  require(balances[msg.sender] > _value) so that no chance of underflow is there. Anyways now this problem is handled by SafeMath and pragma solidity ^0.8.0 .
